  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (5279f69 2022-06-29T00:04:38.931752Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script \n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen running `forge script` to broadcast transactions, receipts in the output logs are unordered. This is a somewhat confusing users experience. It would be better for receipts to ordered naturally. \r\n\r\nFor example, consider the following output: \r\n\r\n```\r\n##\r\nWaiting for receipts.\r\n⠚ [00:00:07] [##################################################################################################] 3/3 receipts (0.0s)\r\n#####\r\n✅ Hash: 0x6a237320ed0630745107cc1cbbfd88c47eeec45f2677d801089bd8cd1dc47ee1\r\nContract Address: 0xa51c1fc2f0d1a1b8494ed1fe312d7c3a78ed91c0\r\nBlock: 11\r\nPaid: 0.000217133256364808 ETH (67066 gas * 3.237605588 gwei)\r\n\r\n\r\n#####\r\n✅ Hash: 0xaf927d14194eed1a112b4796a047c0f9e020c001e42a343b70eeaaaf07a6fa13\r\nContract Address: 0x0dcd1bf9a1b36ce34237eeafef220932846bcd82\r\nBlock: 12\r\nPaid: 0.000217133256364808 ETH (67066 gas * 3.237605588 gwei)\r\n\r\n\r\n#####\r\n✅ Hash: 0x34eb314bae0ebcb76db2b463a5740c6f17f8583a493321edeb3f66354bfd77fb\r\nContract Address: 0xb7f8bc63bbcad18155201308c8f3540b07f84f5e\r\nBlock: 10\r\nPaid: 0.000217133256364808 ETH (67066 gas * 3.237605588 gwei)\r\n```\r\n\r\nTransactions happen on blocks 10, 11 and 12, but receipts appear in the order 11, 12, 10.",
